&lt;div class=&quot;collapsible-block-unfolded-link&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;collapsible-block-link&quot; href=&quot;javascript:;&quot;&gt;▼&amp;nbsp;Author&amp;nbsp;commentary&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;collapsible-block-content&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;My first attempt at GOI Format, first collab, and first not-authored-by-myself article featuring Daniel Asheworth, my main character. This one was really, really fun to write. Probably the most fun I&#039;ve had writing in a very long time.&lt;br /&gt;
Halfway through the writing process &lt;span class=&quot;printuser avatarhover&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uncle-nicolini&quot;  &gt;&lt;img class=&quot;small&quot; src=&quot;http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3487700&amp;amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;amp;timestamp=1610224182&quot; alt=&quot;Uncle Nicolini&quot; style=&quot;background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3487700)&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uncle-nicolini&quot;  &gt;Uncle Nicolini&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; came and said &amp;quot;okay, let me make this good&amp;quot;, and that&#039;s pretty much what happened. I&#039;m really grateful for his help, as he influenced the final shape of the article by a very long shot. This one&#039;s probably my favorite article I&#039;ve written onsite.&lt;/p&gt;
