&lt;div id=&quot;wiki-tab-0-0&quot;&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span&gt;SCP-4051&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Well, here we are. First SCP. The one that started the Deepwell Catalog, even if that wasn&#039;t my intent when I posted it. I&#039;m still surprised people liked it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;4051 is… complex. It&#039;s a story about a teenage vigilante superhero who joins a task force and unlocks a hidden power by the end — and it&#039;s all played straight. I had no aspiration of commenting on well-known tropes which have been known to kill articles on this site. I just wanted to write a story despite them.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;4051 was a cry for help. The Nagiros who posted it was trapped in a hostile setting, tormented by authority figures who should have been looking after her, stuck in a mindspace of passive acceptance and denial.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I&#039;ve had a lot of requests to continue Rainer&#039;s story. As I&#039;ve grown as a person, he&#039;s remained at the sidelines: foraying with &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-4260&quot;&gt;Death&lt;/a&gt;, finding some &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-4415&quot;&gt;friends&lt;/a&gt;, inspiring &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scpwiki.com/systems-patch&quot;&gt;revolution&lt;/a&gt;. I&#039;d like to continue that story.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span&gt;SCP-4175&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I wrote this for Pride Month of 2019 and it&#039;s currently my most popular article. Personally? I don&#039;t think it&#039;s my best work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then again, a lot of people liked it. I know a lot of readers were excited to see the trans pride flag on a featured article — even if it did bring a fair amount of controversy my way.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span&gt;AFTERLIFE OPHIDIAN /// The Foundation Over Heaven&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A poetry-prose piece based in despair. I felt trapped in life, faced by oblivion on all sides, and channeled it into this article.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It exists, I suppose.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span&gt;SCP-4755&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now then, it looks like my pet anomalous science, essophysics, has finally come into its own. The Foundation&#039;s tasted the blood in the water and they aren&#039;t backing down. If the universe rejects them, then the solution is simple: build a better universe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Expect great things in the future.&lt;/p&gt;
